miR_family

Yao Xiao

2/21/2019

read the dataset from TargetScan, and get the human subset

mydata <- read.table("miR_Family_Info.txt", sep="\t", header = TRUE)  
human_data <- mydata[(mydata[,3]==9606),];

count family numbers, and get family name with multiple numbers

family_multi <- data.frame()
human_family_num = 1
j=1
family_name = human_data[1,1]
for (i in 2:dim(human_data)[1]){
  if(human_data[i,1] != human_data[i-1,1]){
    family_name = human_data[i,1]
    human_family_num = human_family_num+1
    if(human_data[i-1,1] == human_data[i-2,1]){
      family_multi[j,1] <- as.character(human_data[i-1,1])
      family_multi[j,2] <- human_data[i-1,6]
      j=j+1
    }
  }
}

extract and analyze g13-g16 sequence within different family

supp_type <- data.frame()
supp_counts <- data.frame()
for (i in 1:dim(family_multi)[1]){
  individual_family <- human_data[human_data[,1]==family_multi[i,1],]
  n = 1
  supp_type[i,n] = substr(individual_family[1,5],13,16)
  supp_counts[i,n] = 1
  for(j in 2:dim(individual_family)[1]){
    new_supp = TRUE
    for(k in 1:n){
      if(substr(individual_family[j,5],13,16) == supp_type[i,k]){
        supp_counts[i,k] = supp_counts[i,k]+1
        new_supp = FALSE
        break
      }
    }
    if( new_supp == TRUE){
      n = n+1
      supp_type[i,n] = substr(individual_family[j,5],13,16)
      supp_counts[i,n] = 1
    }
  }
}

count how many familys have different g13-g16 sequence

num_single_supp_f <- c()
num_multi_supp_f <- c()
j =1
k = 1
for (i in 1:dim(family_multi)[1]){
  individual_family <- human_data[human_data[,1]==family_multi[i,1],]
  if(supp_counts[i,1]==dim(individual_family)[1]){
    num_single_supp_f[j] = i
    j =j+1
  }
  else{
    num_multi_supp_f[k] = i
    k= k+1
  }
}

Pie plot of familys with single or multi supp sites

pie(c(length(num_multi_supp_f),length(num_single_supp_f)),labels = c("128 families with different g13-g16","42 families with same g13-g16"),main = 'Analyze of all multi member families')

Only analyze broadly conserved family (family 1~43)

BC_num_single_supp_f <- num_single_supp_f[num_single_supp_f<=43]
BC_num_multi_supp_f <- num_multi_supp_f[num_multi_supp_f<=43]
pie(c(length(BC_num_multi_supp_f),length(BC_num_single_supp_f)),labels = c("25 families with different g13-g16","18 families with same g13-g16"),main = 'Analyze of Broadly conserved family with multi members')

analyze conserved family (1~56)

C_num_single_supp_f <- num_single_supp_f[num_single_supp_f<=56]
C_num_multi_supp_f <- num_multi_supp_f[num_multi_supp_f<=56]
pie(c(length(C_num_multi_supp_f),length(C_num_single_supp_f)),labels = c("36 families with different g13-g16","20 families with same g13-g16"),main = 'Analyze of conserved family with multi members')

analyze poorly conserved family (57~170)

P_num_single_supp_f <- num_single_supp_f[num_single_supp_f>56]
P_num_multi_supp_f <- num_multi_supp_f[num_multi_supp_f>56]
pie(c(length(P_num_multi_supp_f),length(P_num_single_supp_f)),labels = c("92 families with different g13-g16","22 families with same g13-g16"),main = 'Analyze of Poorly conserved family with multi members')
